history.content: At this point, I'm assuming that the 160 waitlist is full (somebody asked about it earlier iirc), and that 161 hit the 70% cap that they set for enrollments.

When I tried to enroll CS161 and CS160 today, I got these two message 

CS160:

Request not processed. There is no wait list available. The wait list request was not processed, as there are no wait list places available for one or more of the class sections in this request.

CS161

You are unable to enroll in this class at this time. Available seats are reserved and you do not meet the reserve capacity requirements. If a wait list is available, you may still be placed on the waitlist for this class. To do this, select Add Another Class to return to step 1. Select the class link, select the wait list option and resubmit your request.

I declared LSCS as a simultaneous major this semester. And I can actually see that two majors are listed under Academic section on my CalCentral. I don't understand why I still did not meet the requirement. Since there are still seats open for both class, I should be able to enroll in these two courses. 

Can anyone tell me what to do?
history.subject: Couldn't Enroll course because of Enrollment restrictions.
